<paragraph blockId="158.[189,303,267,293]" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="158.[189,1399,314,555]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
The record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephensen" authorityYear="1947" box="[349,488,314,340]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epimeriidae" genus="Epimeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monodon">
<emphasis box="[349,488,314,340]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">E. monodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the eastern shelf of the Weddell Sea at 
<quantity box="[991,1063,314,341]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" unit="m" value="254.0">254 m</quantity>
listed in the data compilation of 
<bibRefCitation author="De Broyer" box="[221,497,350,376]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="De Broyer" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" pagination="1 - 325" refId="ref136532" refString="De Broyer C., Lowry J. K., Jazdzewski K. &amp; Robert H. 2007. Catalogue of the Gammaridean and Corophiidean Amphipoda (Crustacea) of the Southern Ocean with distribution and ecological data. Synopses of the Amphipoda of the Southern Ocean 1: 1 - 325. Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Brussels. Available from www. marinespecies. org / aphia. php? p = sourceget &amp; id = 10098 [accessed 27 Sep. 2016]." type="journal article" year="2007">
De Broyer 
<emphasis box="[352,411,350,376]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
falls outside of the usual geographical and bathymetric range of the species. It is considered as very suspect. It might be based on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coleman" authorityYear="1994" box="[836,1001,385,411]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epimeriidae" genus="Epimeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annabellae">
<emphasis box="[836,1001,385,411]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">E. annabellae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is common at such depth in the eastern Weddell Sea. It seems possible that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephensen" authorityYear="1947" box="[783,926,421,447]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epimeriidae" genus="Epimeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monodon">
<emphasis box="[783,926,421,447]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">E. monodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is a very shallow-water species, uses algal rafting as a method of dispersal between islands and archipelagoes. 
<bibRefCitation author="Thurston" box="[1098,1289,457,483]" firstAuthor="Thurston" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" pagination="1 - 133" refId="ref145646" refString="Thurston M. H. 1972. The Crustacea Amphipoda of Signy Island, South Orkney Islands. British Antarctic Survey Scientific Reports 71: 1 - 133. Available from: http: // nora. nerc. ac. uk / 509215 / 1 / The % 20 crustacea % 20 amphipoda % 20 of % 20 Signy % 20 Island, % 20 South % 20 Orkney % 20 Islands % 20 - % 20 BAS % 20 Scientific % 20 Report % 2071. pdf [accessed 27 Sep. 2016]" type="journal article" year="1972">Thurston (1972)</bibRefCitation>
recorded a slight sexual dimorphism in the species: “the male has larger eyes and a slightly more prominent projection on pleon segment 3”.
</paragraph>
